show how rapid technological advances in batteries and solar technologies are already driving large-scale transformations in power supply, while economic and geopolitical changes, combined with a growing political awareness that there are alternatives to fossil fuels will combine in the coming years to bring an energy revolution ever closer. Within our lifetimes, the authors argue, we will see changes that will reshape economics, the balance of political power, and even the most mundane aspects of our daily lives. Determinedly forward-looking and optimistic, though never straying from hard facts, The Tesla Revolution paints a striking picture of our global energy future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 4aEconomics and Finance. 4aSocial and Political Sciences. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Industries / Energy.2bisacsh  aPeak oil - energy - tesla - solar.1 aMiddelkoop, Willem, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package 2016-2018z978311066731808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backlist 2015-2017z978311060644708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066284940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048531950zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048531950423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048531950.jpg  a978-3-11-060644-7  AUP eBook Package Backlist 2015-2017c2015d2017  a978-3-11-066284-9  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-066731-8  AUP eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMAL